                    The bill would provide billions of dollars in rental and utility assistance to people who are struggling and in danger of being evicted from their homes. About $27 billion would go toward emergency rental assistance. The vast majority of it would replenish the so-called Coronavirus Relief Fund, created by the CARES Act and distributed through state, local and tribal governments,
                    <a href=\"https://nlihc.org/sites/default/files/COVID-Relief-Budget_Reconciliation.pdf\">
